Employees receive training in the procedures to be followed by employees who remain to operate critical plant operations before they evacuate. Maverick Terminals Three Rivers, LLC has around-the-clock communications capability with appropriate emergency response organizations (Fire Department, Police Department, Sheriff's Office, or similar). This interface provides the means of notifying the public of an incident, if necessary, as well as facilitating quick response to an incident. In addition, Maverick Terminals Three Rivers, LLC conducts periodic emergency drills and refresher training for plant personnel.
P. PLANNED CHANGES TO IMPROVE SAFETY
Maverick Terminals Three Rivers, LLC's management is committed to the following:
-Preventing accidents;
-Training our employees in correct response procedures in the event of an accident;
-Participating in community emergency preparedness;
-Addressing any citizen concerns by fully explaining potential hazards associated with Maverick Terminals Three Rivers, LLC operations and all steps being taken to prevent and mitigate accidents
With these objectives in mind, this Risk Management Plan has been developed to provide information about our management of the risks associated with the natural gas treatment and liquids recovery process. Most importantly, we stress our commitment to ensuring a safe operation for our employees, our visitors, and our community.
